LOCALITY: stakeout Brambling Mt. Fury Circle SW, Issaquah (2015)
TRIP COMMENTS: This was my third visit and finally the Brambling cooperated.  This is a house located at 625 Mt. Fury Circle S.W. in Issaquah.  Dan and Fran Pope are gems and welcome birders.  They place seed on the railing of their deck and that is where the Brambling visits - usually with a flock of Juncos.
SPECIES COMMENTS: Bird has been coming to this feeder for almost 3 weeks.  Owners (Dan and Fran Pope) got ID from Cornell and made it known to some local birders.  I learned of it a few days ago and finally saw it today.  First at 10:29 for a few seconds before garbage truck scared it off.  It returned about 20 minutes later and fed on railing for a few minutes - photographed.  Popes said it had come in twice before as well.  Usually comes in with flock of Juncos;.--<iframe src="https://www.flickr.com/photos/127293169@N07/16646357281/in/datetaken/player/" width="500" height="367" frameborder="0"></iframe>
